&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Product&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Vulcan is a cybersecurity solution specifically designed for GenAI, offering two core services: Red Team (vulnerability assessment) and Blue Team (real-time defense). It ensures GenAI compliance, cybersecurity robustness, and operational integrity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Since its official launch in 2024, Vulcan has been recognized by the international standard-setting organization OWASP as a certified vendor for LLM &amp;amp; GenAI security testing and assessment. It is one of the few solutions capable of supporting multiple Asian languages (Traditional Chinese, Simplified Chinese, Japanese, Korean, Thai) and Standard Arabic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134245417&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:240,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a passionate and highly skilled &lt;strong&gt;GenAI Security Researcher&lt;/strong&gt; to join our team. You will conduct applied and theoretical research into AI vulnerabilities, attack/defense methods, and security/safety benchmarking. Your work will directly shape our AI safety products, contribute to research communities, and influence industry standards and regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research: Investigate adversarial attacks, data poisoning, prompt injection, jailbreaks, and other AI system vulnerabilities in multi-modalities (e.g., text, image, video, and audio). Design and evaluate mitigation strategies, including fine-tuning, guardrails, content filtering, and robust model architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benchmarking: Develop and maintain AI security evaluation frameworks, datasets, and performance metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration: Partner with product and partnership teams to integrate the findings into our AI security solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dissemination: Publish findings in top-tier conferences and journals, present at industry events, and contribute to open-source initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research skills: Advanced degree (e.g., MSc/PhD) with strong analytical thinking, problem-solving skills, and ability to translate research into practical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge: Deep understanding of relevant techniques, such as generative AI, security &amp;amp; privacy, computer vision, signal processing, and human-computer interaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication skills: Clearly explain complex concepts in layman&#39;s terms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in English: Write and read documents, communicate with team members in English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teamwork: Work closely with our members to deliver value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agility: Adapt quickly to changing research priorities and emerging AI security threats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coding skills: Proficiency in Python and experience with experimentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&g

